                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On January 29, 1954, Senator <persName corresp="#p_SSJC1">John C.
                        Stennis</persName> of Mississippi, member of the Senate Committee on Armed
                    Services, transmitted a letter to <persName corresp="#p_WCE1">Charles E.
                        Wilson</persName>, Secretary of Defense, expressing opposition to
                    participation by the United States in the war in Indochina. For text, see <hi
                        rend="italic">United States-Vietnam Relations, 1945–1967</hi>, Book 9, page
                    239.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
